        },
        "subject": "LU-10107 clio: truncate PFL file at component boundary",
        "message": "LU-10107 clio: truncate PFL file at component boundary\n\nTruncate I/O used to be sent to overlapping components of\n[size, eof), however this is problematic when the file is\ntruncated up to component boundary and if the next component\nis not instantiated yet.\n\nThis patch will change to send truncate RPC to overlapping\ncomponents by [size - 1, eof).\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: If414b058804e68efb463d64d8cd1aca66b4f721d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
